title: [Health] Magnetic slime robot could be deployed inside the body to perform tasks such as retrieving objects swallowed by accident

[Health] New research shows survival rate improvement for extremely pre-term infants: 30.0% at 22 weeks and 55.8% at 23 weeks, a considerably higher rate of survival than between 2008-2012, in which survival to discharge was 7% for live-born infants at 22 weeks and 32% for live-born infants at 23 weeks
